The paper discusses a new class of lossy compression based on statistical similarity, which is relevant to data compression (cs.DC) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also presents compression performance analyses and investigates the difference between two transform techniques, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses data reconstruction quality using spectral analysis, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE).
